<br>
1.  It's dangerous to innocent bystanders.  If you walk past a Wizard or Druid Quad Kiting, their kite doesn't turn on you.  If you walk past a Swarm Kite, it does!<br>
2.  It hogs content that could be used by one or more full groups.<br>
3.  It's overpowered.  No class should have that magnitude of soloing power in a grouping game.  Yes, other classes are similiarly overpowered.  No, that doesn't make it right. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">[65 Maestro] <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111714">Keiz Dinzyar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (Wood Elf) &lt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.talionis.com">Talionis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&gt;<br>
