<br>
Unless they figure out a way (reduce the range perhaps) to make charm usable for crowd control but not overpowered from an EXP perspective I would not be surprised if we do not get one in the expasion at all (ie remove the song entry). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=montgomery0>Montgomery0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 4:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19466.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sony's song thread</span><hr size=1> Of course there's a simple way to make a charm without swarmkiting.  Our mana regen is limited to 19 mana per tick.  Swarmkiting deals with charms that have a duration of 10-20 seconds, just enough time for your pet to get beaten down to within an inch of it's life.  Currently, the cost of our charms is a lot lower than that of our maximum mana regen; so with even a few +mana regen items, a bard can continuously charm for extended periods of time.<br>
<br>
Having a charm with a large mana cost would make swarmkiting unfeasible.  Even to make the cost equal to our mana regen would work (I think double cost would be the best choice.)  <br>
<br>
For example, a charm with an MR debuff (to make it last long,) slow component and lasting two minutes, with a mana cost of 38 x 2(10) = 760 (that's maximum mana regen x2 over two minutes (10 tics per minute,)) would make swarm kiting work for only the first few mobs in a swarm kite.  If it took you 4 ticks to get your mob down to chanting range, it would take you 36 ticks (about 3.6 minutes) to regain that mana back.  Depending on your maximum manapool, you would only be able to kill a very few mobs through swarmkiting until you needed to med up to try again, each successive swarmkite taking 3.6 minutes after going out of mana in this example.<br>
<br>
With this charm, you could again crowd control with charm and have it last a long while with very little chance of it being used to swarm kite.  It has been mentioned before, but I think it's just a case of see no evil = do no evil on the developers' part. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=falundirxviento>Falundir X Viento</A></span><br> Posts: 168<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 5:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19466.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ameritech.net/users/larva_7/aknight.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sony's song thread</span><hr size=1> In this day and age of whacky coding, it probally wouldnt be that hard to add a new definition for determining if a player is in a group, and then making a specific spell only active while in group.<br>
