<br>
And making a huge mana cost on charm would make it worse than useless...pull expecting to charm a mob, 3 fizzles later you're OOM and you've got that extra mob pissed at you.  A reuse timer is just as bad, because then one resist or early break and you're screwed again.  <br>
<br>
One way that WOULD work is to make it so that no more than 1 or 2 mobs can attack any charmed pet at the same time.  Preferrably only pets that were charmed with the new (presumeably higher cap) charm song.  <br>
<br>
A better idea is to include a &quot;damage shield&quot; rider on the charm song that causes hate reduction.  So every time a mob hits your pet, the pet loses 100 aggro, and the mob becomes more likely to go after you or another party member instead.  The entire swarm would go after the bard pretty quick.  <br>
<br>
Alternately, if that's not codeable, the pet could have a frequent hate reduction proc, so as it hits mobs they lose interest in it and run after the bard.  <br>
<br>
Both of the last suggestions would make aggro+pet kiting far easier for bards though, which Verant may not like as much, but it would still be no better than necro or chanter or druid aggro kiting, and it would totally kill the ability to swarm with the new song. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vopiululant>Vopi Ululant</A></span><br> Posts: 418<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 6:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19466.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/uf/Vasudeva/kitten_eye.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sony's song thread</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2. It hogs content that could be used by one or more full groups.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
