<br>
That said, the prevelence of it is not nearly enough IMHO to offset the loss of charming for other needs. Charmed mob fighting is something that is standard practice in the game for chanters and druids, and quite often for Mages too in the right places.<br>
<br>
Frankly, until they get a way to address swarm kiting specifically, I think they need to just accept it as a pain and otherwise continue on with things. That said, the idea here of putting a maximum number of mobs that will attack your pet without going straight for you instead is a terrific way of addressing this. The code for it really shouldn't be all that difficult, and it would be highly effective I suspect. I would make the number fairly high - say 4 or 5 - but implment it in that fashion. Yes, at 4 or 5 swarm kiting could still be feasible, but it would not be anywhere near as out of balance, and, as such, be attractive to even fewer than it already is, while at the same time still keep charm parking a very viable option. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=485847" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.belain.com/files/singsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
