<br>
1: it's something specific bard. Which means it makes us unique. Yes, others envy us for it, but compared to AoE kyting and/or other solo powers of the various classes,... it isn't overpowered.<br>
<br>
2: it's powerfull, yet not without danger. All of you should know the only way to really learn swarming is by dieing. Now, you tell me that's without danger? Also, a small biting piece of lag = dead bard. And, how many never have that. This isn't as true to other ways of soloing where you only agro 1 mob, as 1 mob isn't as deadly.<br>
<br>
3: it took me some time to master, and it's a good to have mastered it. And, the feeling of being 'in control' of so many mobs,...<br>
<br>
4: there's an argument where people complain about the risk for others it poses,.... please do explain how someone walking into a group of 10+ mobs is NOT asking for trouble. When I go and run around in BoT, (or several other places) and suddenly have a see-invisser in my neck thanks to a friendly neighbourhood mage, do I complain about the mage, or about my lack of conning the mob?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In the end: I think it's one of the more fun things to do in this game. And I wouldn't like it to be taken away. Really not. :-)<br>
